RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 79. Claiming Purse 29000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Conside red For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MENTORING while in hand took control on the inside at the half, opened up at will unchallenged through the turn, cruised home for the win drifting out when throttled down in deep stretch, was pulled up galloping out and was vanned off. FOREST STAR travelled in mid-pack in the early stages, was roused gaining momentum into the turn, was urged for more left handed nearing the quarter pole and gamely bested the rest to be a non threatening runner up in the end. HIP TO YOUR TRICKS settled to be second last down the backside, put a mild run around horses three wide at the quarter marker, swung out widest in the six path at the top of the lane and finished with intent in deep stretch to capture third in a three way photo. CANDY STREET trailed down the back straight, began to get involved picking up runners on the rail at the quarter pole, angled out to the three path turning for home, showed good late interest and just missed getting up for third at the wire. YORKVILLE stalked near the rear inside down the backstretch, advanced two wide at the three furlong marker, shifted outside for the drive in the five path battling for a piece of the prize and had to settle on the fringes when outfinished in deep stretch for the show money. SNOOKERED broke sharp on the break, settled outside runners stalking in midfield down the backside, could not quicken with others around the bend, was shuffled back seeing the field turning for home and finished up mildly to be involved for the minor share in the end. TRIGGER'S BAY had a brief lead in the early going, gave way to the winner inside to chase at the half, was urged for more to keep up with the winner through the turn and retreated on the fence at the furlong marker. READY ON THE LINE had a good position down the backside all alone tracing the front duo, was asked for more run midturn, offered little response inside and emptied out in upper stretch.

FOREST FLASH settled in mid-pack on the rail down the backside, was asked for more run midway on the turn, offered little gain and yielded in upper stretch. GLORIOUS REVENGE trailed the field down the backstretch, lost contact with the pack running on the turn and could not reach contention driving to the finish line.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNCLE TRULY advanced on the rail getting a better forward position with five eighths remaining, was nudged three furlongs out keeping pace with rivals, began to reel in runners in upper stretch, burst on by the leader on the fence at the furlong pole and was extending the advantage at the finish. SOUPER ATTENTIVE was content to track the speed outside throughout the turn, bid for the lead outside at the top of the stretch, assumed command with three sixteenths to go, could not match strides with the winner on the rail with an eighth to run and and finished up besting the rest easily for a clear second in the end. NANTUCKETS DAY travelled the wide outside runners in mid-pack five furlongs from the line, was shuffled back some to be near the rear inside running on the turn, began to pick up runners driving on the fence in upper stretch, shifted outside off the tiring early leader at the eighth pole and closed belatedly to be an easy but non threatening third at the wire. SILENT AND VIOLENT settled in midfield three wide on the turn, was asked for more three furlongs out but could not make up any ground on the leaders, continued to be hard ridden by his rider starting to gain on tiring foes in upper stretch and ran on mildly in the late stages for a small piece on the prize at the finish. VITALITY broke with the field at the start, was void of early run to trail down the backstretch, was allowed to find his stride unhurried seeing the pack around the turn, began to figure things out starting a rally shifting inwards at the sixteenth pole and offered a good late finish reaching for ground at the wire. JO DADDY settled in the third flight all alone rating kindly watching the front three with five eighths to go, comfortably tracked the leader running around the turn, pounced outside in the four path turning for home, battled for the lead in upper stretch but levelled off in the final seventy yards losing a few positions at the wire. JOHNNY GOLD assumed command down the backside, set a modest pace running on the turn while under no pressure, was engulfed outside at the top of the lane and backed away through the field at the furlong pole. HARD DIAMOND was steadied in the three path between runners down the backside at the three quarters pole, made little progress running on the fence throughout the turn, shifted outside under a ride at the top of the lane but could not offer a finishing kick and was not persevered with in the final furlong.

CATHOLIC JACKIE stalked close to the back of the pack outside in the early going, put a mild run three wide with five sixteenths from the finish and could not offer a closing rally down the stretch. SNIPER JACK travelled in the second flight three wide on the outside down the back straight, was roused trying to keep pace with quickening foes at the quarter marker, could not find more to give driving to the finish and gave way in the five path in upper stretch. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRIPOLINA tracked between rivals in the second flight three wide down the back straight, lost some momentum and positioning three eighths from the wire, recovered quickly to pounce outside widest in the five path driving for the wire, was set down at the eighth pole under left handed urging and drew off comfortably for a convincing win in deep stretch. TWO GHOSTS tracked in the second flight outside foes four deep down the backstretch, rallied four wide three furlongs out getting a jump on the winner, making a bold move around horses at the quarter pole bid for the lead in the four path turning for home, dueled with the winner until the furlong marker and gave way late to be second best on this day. WESTERN WHIRL prompted the pace three wide outside rivals down the back straight, battled in the three path between horses for the lead two furlongs out, fought on gamely in the hunt up front at the top of the stretch, faded from the top two finishers with a sixteenth to run inside and kept to the task at the line to win the bob for third money in the end. BREAK THE SPELL was allowed to settle down the backside trailing the field, began to extend his stride midway on the turn, picked up runners outside at the quarter pole and finished with good intent to close in late, just missing third money in a tight photo. MAGIC SLIPS contested for the lead on the rail down the backstretch, maintained a slim advantage setting a brisk pace on the fence travelling on the turn, was collared outside straightening out for the drive, could not find another gear in mid-stretch and faded at the furlong pole. GOTTS GOT IT broke in at the start, was in the mix between the leaders down the backstretch, was roused for more, battling with rivals on either side five sixteenths from home, could not keep pace with others quickening pace at the quarter pole and yielded behind horses in the three path in upper stretch. BANKINGONAMIRACLE was nestled on the fence watching the trio at the half, lost inside position into the turn and was shuffled back three furlongs from the wire, tried to play catch up hustled on the fence running around the bend but could not get involved running down the stretch. KING OF THE TRACK was bumped outside on the break, settled near the rear in a tightly compacted bunch at the half, offered a mild run between runners in midturn when asked for run but could not more at the top of the lane and weakened on the fence in mid-stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRIDEOFDISTINCTION stalked near the rear in the early stages, began to lengthen his stride reaching for more ground down the backstretch, closed the gap smartly on the leaders with a half left to run, swung outside straightening out for the drive in the six path, closed in on the leaders in mid-stretch, took control at the furlong marker and just held from his stablemate at the wire. MEYER travelled throughout tracked the leaders nestled on the rail in the second flight, had to wait at the top of the stretch behind the weakening early leader at the top of the stretch, swung outside to the six path at the furlong marker, found another gear late and surged at the wire but could not get there in time. RON'S GIZMO was situated just outside in the tracking second flight for most of the race, angled outside to make his bid in the four path at the top of the lane, battled in upper stretch for the lead, drifted inwards driving to the finish in the final eighth still in the hunt but faded in the final seventy yards to hold for third after the marathon. CANADIAN PHAROAH stalked outside the winner in the fourth flight down the backstretch, could not keep pace with the winner starting to make a run with three quarters to go, shuffled back some with a half to the wire, found more three furlongs out gaining on tiring foes and finished up one paced down the lane to garner a minor share in the end. LIL BIT GANGSTA sat alone in the third flight down the backside, made an early move going five wide at the top of the stretch, took command at the three sixteenths marker, could not sustain the run at the eighth pole and stalled between runners in deep stretch. CUPID'S CLAWS settled near the rear down the back straight, made little headway on the final turn while and showed some late interest to close in willingly in the final furlong. SIR SAHIB trailed the field throughout, swung outside in the seven path when with two furlongs from the wire, could not offer a finishing kick but did run on to pass the tiring early leaders down the stretch. POINT TO THE STARS hounded the frontrunner outside down the backstretch to even at times get his head in front, could not find more between rivals when others were picking up the pace with five sixteenths to run and stopped in upper stretch. LORD OF WAR set the pace inside while hounded outside for the first mile and a quarter, began to edge away from the early pace foes with five sixteenths to go, was collared outside at the quarter pole, offered no resistance in upper stretch on the fence, tired at the furlong marker and galloped across the finish.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LA BELLEZA NEGRA got away well, went straight to the front and sped clear, shifted in to dictate terms near the inside, had enough in reserve to spurt away in upper stretch and hold sway. CITY MISCHIEF bumped a rival at the start, angled in and advanced inside up the backstretch to a more forward position, came out five wide in upper stretch and a bit wider thereafter, finished strongly to gain the place. RAT PORTAGE was within range two to three wide, kept on in the stretch but needed more late. SCOOT DADDY was caught five to six wide on the turn, swung out ten deep turning for home, was gaining but too late. FOUR ACES HIGH was coaxed forward to track from inside foes racing just off the rail on the turn, moved out four wide turning for home, lacked the needed late kick. NOT SO QUIET exchanged a light bump at the start, settled off the pace two to three wide, angled inside a rival at the top of the stretch, showed good late interest. LIGHT THE LAMP raced mid-pack going five to six wide on the turn, came out eight to nine wide for the drive, needed more late. RED LINE OVERDRIVE raced off the pace toward the rear four wide through the turn, ran on mildly to improve. SPITE STORE chased in behind four wide on the turn, weakened in the stretch. WEALLLIKEDHIM stalked four to five wide through the turn, faded in the stretch. PRICELESS WILL switched off the inside, moved out eight deep turning into upper stretch, shifted in for room in mid-stretch, ran on. MAAKWA was hard to load, bumped at the start, raced at the back, swung eight wide turning for home, failed to menace. BOSSY HOLIDAY exchanged a light bump at the start, raced off the inside about four deep through the turn, failed to menace. AIM FOR THE SKY stalked three to four wide, came up empty.
